---

---

<section class="py-[120px] bg-surface-container-low">
    <div class="max-w-[1296px] mx-auto px-4 md:px-8 lg:px-16">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-16">
            <div class="w-10 h-0.5 bg-secondary"></div>
            <span
                class="font-label-caps text-label-caps text-secondary tracking-widest"
                >LATEST RELEASE</span
            >
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-4 md:gap-8 items-center">
            <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-5">
                <div class="relative inline-block hard-shadow">
                    <img
                        class="w-full aspect-[2/3] object-cover"
                        src="./trust_no_one_2d.jpg"
                        alt="Trust No One book cover"
                    />
                    <div
                        class="absolute top-0 left-0 bg-secondary text-white px-4 py-2 font-label-caps text-[10px] tracking-widest"
                    >
                        BOOK FOUR
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div
                class="col-span-12 md:col-span-6 md:col-start-7 flex flex-col justify-center"
            >
                <p
                    class="font-label-caps text-label-caps text-secondary mb-3 tracking-widest"
                >
                    THE CONOR THORN SERIES
                </p>
                <h2
                    class="font-headline-lg text-headline-lg text-primary font-bold mb-2 tracking-tight"
                >
                    Trust No One
                </h2>
                <p
                    class="font-headline-md text-xl text-on-surface-variant font-normal mb-8"
                >
                    by Glenn Dyer
                </p>

                <div class="w-10 h-0.5 bg-secondary mb-8"></div>

                <p
                    class="font-body-lg text-body-lg text-on-surface-variant mb-6 leading-relaxed"
                >
                    When a decoded German transmission points to a traitor
                    inside Allied command, OSS agent Conor Thorn is dispatched
                    into occupied France—where trust is a death sentence and
                    every contact may already be compromised.
                </p>
                <p class="font-body-lg text-body-lg text-zinc-400 mb-10 italic">
                    "A propulsive, masterfully crafted WWII thriller." — Chris
                    Wallace, CNN
                </p>

                <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
                    <a
                        href="/books/trust-no-one"
                        class="bg-secondary text-white px-8 py-3 font-label-caps text-label-caps tracking-widest hover:bg-on-surface hover:text-background transition-colors"
                        >ORDER NOW</a
                    >
                    <a
                        href="/books/trust-no-one"
                        class="border border-outline-variant text-on-surface-variant px-8 py-3 font-label-caps text-label-caps tracking-widest hover:border-primary hover:text-primary transition-colors"
                        >LEARN MORE</a
                    >
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
